# Phase 0.11 — Final Phase 0 Verification & Sign-off Rules

This rule applies only to Phase 0.11.

## Scope

Phase 0.11 is the final verification and sign-off gate for Phase 0.

The goal is to verify that all Phase 0 deliverables from subphases 0.1 through 0.10 are present and working together as a clean local Docker Compose stack.

This phase is primarily a validation and documentation phase.

## Allowed changes

Allowed files to create or update:

* `docs/phases/step-0.11.md`
* `.cursor/rules/phase-0-11-final-verification.mdc`
* `README.md`, only if a tiny final Phase 0 status note or validation command correction is required

## Verification scope

Verify:

* Root README onboarding flow
* `.env.example` → `.env` workflow
* Docker Compose config validity
* Clean Docker build
* Full stack startup
* nginx as the local entrypoint
* frontend through nginx on `http://localhost`
* backend through nginx on `http://localhost/api/...`
* direct backend health, if accessible
* direct frontend access, if intentionally exposed
* all four FastAPI agent health endpoints
* Postgres health
* Redis health
* Celery worker health or operational status
* Celery beat health or operational status, if present
* Agent containers start without import errors
* Development override exists and does not break the stack
* Final `git status` is clean except for intentional Phase 0.11 documentation/rule changes

## Constraints

Do not implement missing Phase 0 features in this phase.

Do not add nginx behavior.

Do not add new application healthchecks.

Do not change agent Docker build contexts.

Do not add or redesign dev bind mounts.

Do not implement backend, frontend, agent, tenant, auth, Celery, LLM, or business logic features.

Do not hardcode Prestia-specific behavior.

Do not mark Phase 0 as complete if any final acceptance criterion fails.

If verification fails, document the failure clearly in `docs/phases/step-0.11.md` and mark Phase 0 as not ready for sign-off.

## Sign-off rule

Phase 0 may be marked complete only if all final Phase 0 acceptance criteria pass.

If any required service fails to build, start, become healthy, or respond on the expected route, Phase 0 must remain incomplete and the blocker must be documented.

## Documentation expectations

`docs/phases/step-0.11.md` must document:

* Goal
* Scope
* Verification environment
* Files reviewed
* Commands executed
* Results by service
* Final acceptance checklist
* Any failures or known limitations
* Git status
* Final decision: Phase 0 complete or Phase 0 not complete

Do not fabricate command results. If a command cannot be run, document it as not run and explain why.
